  "text": "3.3. Dunkl Laplace-Runge-Lenz vector. In addition to the angular momentum symmetry, the standard Coulomb model possesses a hidden symmetry known as Runge-Lenz or Laplace vector. In the presence of extra non-local Calogero-Moser potential term this vector can be defined by making use of Dunkl operators. For the Calogero-Moser-Coulomb nonlocal problem related to the root system R = A N −1 this conserved quantity was introduced in [CITATION_1] . Now we extend this construction to an arbitrary root system R. We define components A i of a vector A = (A 1 , . . . , A N ) by the formula (23)",
